messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full HTTP request path: /printshop

- All HTTP methods acceptable: false

- HEAD: false
- POST: false
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- The handler method is annotated exactly as:
  @RequestMapping(value = "/printshop", method = RequestMethod.GET)
  in ManagerController.getManagerPrintShop. That defines the path "/printshop" and restricts the mapping to the GET method.
- There is no class-level @RequestMapping on ManagerController that would add a prefix, so the full path is exactly "/printshop".
- Per the instruction to base acceptability on the code (not on implicit framework behavior), only the explicitly declared RequestMethod (GET) is considered acceptable. Therefore HEAD, OPTIONS, and other methods are marked false even though some frameworks may implicitly handle them.
